Post-Match Reflections: Scottie Barnes: 'Well, we got beat by 30, so not very well'

RJ Barrett: 'I think we just didn’t play hard enough, top to bottom. We have to figure it out. Just playing hard, just being that team that we were at the beginning, fighting, we didn’t have our fight tonight, so that’s disappointing.'

Darko Rajakovic: 'Our closeouts were not good. Every time we were supposed to rotate and close out to the three-point line to break the rhythm and to take away threes, we did not do a good enough job of that.... That's something that we're working on, and we're going to continue pounding the rock with that.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Giannis Antetokounmpo put up a triple-double with 11 points, 12 rebounds and 13 assists
RJ Barrett returned to the Raptors' lineup with 25 points and nine rebounds
Toronto shot 9-of-35 from three-point range, including 4-of-26 in the first three quarters
Toronto lost 128-104 to the Bucks, dropping their 13th game in their past 14 starts
Former Raptor Gary Trent Jr. had 17 points on 6-of-9 shooting, including 3-of-5 from three-point range
Backup centre Bruno Fernando is expected to be waived
Milwaukee rookie centre Liam Robbins, Erin Devlin's nephew, made his professional debut in Toronto
